<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="189" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,617,1398]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,725,750]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[327,475,725,750]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="385 - 406" refId="ref10940" refString="Stock, J. H. (1966) Pycnogonida. Campagne de la Calypso au large des cotes atlantiques de l'Amerique du Sud (1961 - 1962). I. Annales de l'Institute Oceanographique, 44, 385 - 406." type="journal article" year="1966">Stock (1966)</bibRefCitation>
reported many specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mane-Garzon" authorityYear="1944" box="[821,957,726,750]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Colossendeidae" genus="Colossendeis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[821,957,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">C. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected by the RV 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1300,725,750]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Calypso" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1300,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Calypso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<date box="[1310,1436,725,750]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" value="1961" valueMax="1962">1961–1962</date>
cruise station 172. Due to the mixing of materials, he reported specimens belonging to this species collected in one or more of six additional stations from that cruise (105, 149, 160, 161, 171 and 173) between 
<collectingRegion box="[1193,1357,797,822]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1368,1436,797,822]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[198,460,833,858]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Buenos Aires Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[470,585,833,858]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,617,1398]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">
<bibRefCitation author="Larramendy, M. L." box="[199,418,869,894]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="149 - 152" refId="ref9370" refString="Larramendy, M. L. (1974) Anotaciones sobre Colossendeis geoffroyi (Mane-Garzon, 1944). Neotropica, 20 (63), 149 - 152." type="journal article" year="1974">Larramendy (1974)</bibRefCitation>
identified 
<specimenCount box="[542,695,869,894]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" type="generic">18 specimens</specimenCount>
from Argentinean waters (
<geoCoordinate box="[1000,1106,870,894]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" precision="925" value="-37.383335">37°23´S–</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[1106,1195,870,894]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" precision="925" value="-40.016666">40°01´S</geoCoordinate>
) collected by the RV 
<emphasis box="[151,329,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Walther Herwig</emphasis>
(
<date box="[343,471,905,930]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" value="1966" valueMax="1971">1966–1971</date>
) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mane-Garzon" authorityYear="1944" box="[516,648,906,930]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Colossendeidae" genus="Colossendeis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[516,648,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">C. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He indicated that these do not differ from the original description, but complemented the description with additional details.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,617,1398]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[199,346,977,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="113 - 139" refId="ref11122" refString="Stock, J. H. (1992) Pycnogonida from southern Brazil. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 135, 113 - 139." type="journal article" year="1992">Stock (1992)</bibRefCitation>
reported one fragmented specimen from the coast of 
<collectingRegion box="[963,1129,977,1002]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[1146,1249,977,1002]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" precision="925" value="-23.416666">23°25´S–</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[1249,1351,977,1002]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" precision="925" value="-43.0">43°00´W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity box="[1364,1436,978,1002]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" unit="m" value="113.0">113 m</quantity>
depth), that he assigned with doubts to 
<emphasis box="[585,725,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mane-Garzon" authorityYear="1944" box="[585,721,1014,1038]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Colossendeidae" genus="Colossendeis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">C. geoffroyi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
He commented that “if…really this species, the range would be considerably extended in northward direction”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,617,1398]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[199,343,1085,1110]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="113 - 139" refId="ref11122" refString="Stock, J. H. (1992) Pycnogonida from southern Brazil. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 135, 113 - 139." type="journal article" year="1992">Stock (1992)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the material reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Minnard, V. &amp; Zamponi, M. O." box="[742,1054,1085,1110]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="257 - 279" refId="ref10132" refString="Minnard, V. &amp; Zamponi, M. O. (1984) Estudios sistematicos de algunos Pantopodos de la region subantartica. Historia Natural, 4 (28), 257 - 279." type="journal article" year="1984">Minnard &amp; Zamponi (1984)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mane-Garzon" authorityYear="1944" box="[1090,1222,1086,1110]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Colossendeidae" genus="Colossendeis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[1090,1222,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">C. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to belong to a different species, given the differences illustrated by the Argentinean authors: “tarsus is [illustrated as being] almost twice as long as propodus; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mane-Garzon" authorityYear="1944" box="[599,736,1158,1182]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Colossendeidae" genus="Colossendeis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[599,736,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">C. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both parts are almost equal in length”. Moreover, the data associated with that material is dubious. The RV 
<emphasis box="[696,875,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Walther Herwig</emphasis>
station 340 (cruise 1966) is not at 
<quantity box="[1260,1331,1194,1218]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
depth, as reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Minnard, V. &amp; Zamponi, M. O." box="[294,623,1229,1254]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="257 - 279" refId="ref10132" refString="Minnard, V. &amp; Zamponi, M. O. (1984) Estudios sistematicos de algunos Pantopodos de la region subantartica. Historia Natural, 4 (28), 257 - 279." type="journal article" year="1984">Minnard &amp; Zamponi (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, but 
<quantity box="[686,761,1229,1254]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" unit="m" value="165.0">165 m</quantity>
depth; furthermore it is not located off Mar del Plata, as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stock, J. H." box="[295,443,1265,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" pagination="113 - 139" refId="ref11122" refString="Stock, J. H. (1992) Pycnogonida from southern Brazil. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 135, 113 - 139." type="journal article" year="1992">Stock (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, but instead is off southern 
<collectingCountry box="[752,863,1265,1290]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[878,984,1265,1290]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" precision="925" value="-53.95">53°57´S–</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[984,1088,1265,1290]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" precision="925" value="-58.766666">58°46´W</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,617,1398]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">
López de 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopez de Levy, M." box="[316,458,1302,1326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" refId="ref9588" refString="Lopez de Levy, M. (1989) Picnogonida (sic). Facultad de Humanidades y Ciencias, Universidad de la Republica, Montevideo, 112 pp." type="book" year="1989">Levy (1989)</bibRefCitation>
gave a general description of females attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mane-Garzon" authorityYear="1944" box="[1063,1199,1302,1326]" class="Pycnogonida" family="Colossendeidae" genus="Colossendeis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pantopoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[1063,1199,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="189">C. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mañé-garzón, 1944, obtained as by-catch in the commercial fishery off the La Plata River (Uruguay-Argentina, 35°–39°S) (López de Levy, pers. comm. to FS 2005).
</paragraph>
